Launched in 2012, the Global Citizen Festival is an extension of the Global Poverty Project, an international advocacy group that hopes to end poverty by increasing the number of people who actively fight it.
To get a free ticket to the event (unless you want to pay for a VIP ticket), attendees had to complete a series of tasks or 'actions' such as volunteering, sending an email to a world leader, making a phone call or otherwise connecting to help raise awareness of their poverty eradication goal.
