He said, "To this day, the feeling of inferiority and being different from others are actually the things that give me energy and strength to succeed".
He wanted to prove he was "something", he said, so he wouldn't disappoint anyone when he eventually learned of his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist has become an active participant in LGBT campaigns and used his participation in this year's Commonwealth Games in Australia to call for more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he did it because he was happy to live in the open, without consequences, and he wanted to inspire hope in others.
