Foreign buyers will be charged a higher coat of arms tax on the purchase of real estate in the UK
Under new plans by the Conservatives, foreign buyers will be charged a higher stamp duty on purchases of UK property, with the extra money to help the homeless.
This move will neutralize the success of Corbyn's efforts to attract young voters.
The increase in stamp duty will affect those who do not pay taxes in Britain
